== Requirements

1. Have a Amazon EC2 image available (AMI)
2. Create an Amazon EBS volume
3. Install the gem: $ sudo gem install Fingertips-backup --source http://gems.github.com

== Configure

1. in the home folder of the user that will run the backups (root), create a .backup dir and add:
   * config.yml
   * Depending on what you configured in config.yml, you could add the required Amazon private key and certificate files
   